# Changelog

All notable changes to DINOForge will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Fixed — URP material crash guard in AssetSwap
- **Prevented a live material crash path on HRV2/URP when a swapped bundle material uses legacy shaders** — `TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` now validates the resolved material shader before assigning it to `RenderMesh`. Materials whose shader name is not prefixed with `Universal Render Pipeline/` and that do not expose SRP batcher support via `FindPassTagValue` are skipped from live material assignment, while mesh swaps still proceed when valid. Skipped bundles log once (`[AssetSwap] skipped material swap for X: shader Y not HRV2-compatible`) and fallback to no-op material assignment. Crash-risk runtime writes are therefore prevented without blocking mesh-only swaps. File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`.

### Fixed — Asset Swap: per-frame "already loaded" AssetBundle flood (#992)
- **Per-frame Unity error flood `The AssetBundle '…sw-rep-clone-engineer' can't be loaded because another AssetBundle with the same files is already loaded`** — `AssetSwapSystem.LoadBundle` called `AssetBundle.LoadFromFile` and, when the LRU cache (max 10) evicted+Unloaded a bundle that Unity still considered loaded (Unload lag / scene-transition skip), the next frame's re-load threw and Unity logged the error. Because the swap retries every pending request each frame, this repeated forever — **740 occurrences** in a single skirmish run, flooding `Player.log` and degrading the game. Fixes in `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`: (1) **already-loaded recovery** — `LoadBundle` now catches the "already loaded" throw and reuses the existing handle via `AssetBundle.GetAllLoadedAssetBundles()` (matched by bundle name), re-caching it so later passes hit the cache and never re-call `LoadFromFile`; (2) **negative-result cache** (`_permanentlyFailedBundles`) — a bundle that yields no usable Mesh/Material (the 13 #986 90-byte stubs) or hard-fails to load is marked permanently failed and skipped on every later frame (logged once, then silent), cleared on `ScheduleReset` so hot-reloaded fixed bundles retry. Live-verified after deploy (build hash `CEA2362E…`, clean skirmish): `Player.log` "already loaded" count **740 → 0** (entire 2273-line run, 0 occurrences, 0 clone-engineer mentions, 0 AssetBundle errors). Working swaps intact — **306 `entity swap result=True`**, ground units `swapped 100/100` across 17264 matching entities, `sw-rep-clone-engineer` cim swap `result=True`. File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`.
### Fixed — SW UNIT bundles now carry real URP Lit materials (0 unit swaps → fixed)
- **Root cause (silent prefab-gen failure):** SW *unit* bundles rendered native in-game because their prefab materials referenced Unity's **built-in default/error shader** (`m_Shader: {fileID: 46, guid: 0000000000000000f000000000000000}`), which DINO's Hybrid Renderer V2 shader-guard rejects → 0 unit swaps. Three competing Editor builders existed; the dedicated unit builder `BuildSwMissingBundles.Build` resolved its source meshes via `AssetDatabase.FindAssets("<fbx> t:Model", "Assets/Models")`, but **`Assets/Models/` is empty** (no glTF importer in the project; the 44 `.glb` live under `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/raw/`). Every def hit `MISSING FBX → continue`, so the prefab was never regenerated and the build re-bundled the stale built-in-shader prefab (`Shaders 0.0 kb` symptom). Likewise `BuildAll.Run` only upgraded a material **inside** its `[skip] existing-prefab` guard, so all 75 pre-existing primitive prefabs kept their non-URP materials.
- **Fix (file+line):**
  - `unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Editor/BuildSwMissingBundles.cs` — replaced the `MISSING FBX → continue` silent-skip with a **primitive fallback** (Capsule) so every unit prefab is always regenerated with a URP material applied; build now exits 0 even when no real mesh is present (URP material is the load-bearing fix; mesh fidelity is a follow-up requiring a glTF importer).
  - `unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Editor/BuildAll.cs` — added `EnsureUrpMaterial(key, folder, color)` called for **every** def *before* the prefab-existence `[skip]` check, so pre-existing prefabs' materials are upgraded to URP/Lit in-place (prefab references material by GUID, so in-place upgrade is sufficient).
- **Verification (real, not "built N"):** Ran headless `Unity 2021.3.45f1` (one instance at a time, lockfile cleared): `BuildSwMissingBundles.Build` → `GenerateStarWarsPrefabsFromModels.Generate` → `BuildAll.Run`, each `-logFile`. `sw-shader-report.log` shows **19/19 unit materials = `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit`, 0 Standard**. The git diff of e.g. `sw-b1-squad.mat` confirms the on-disk shader moved from the built-in error shader (`guid 0000…f000…`) to URP/Lit (`guid 933532a4fcc9baf4fa0491de14d08ed7`, the URP `Lit.shader` GUID) with full URP material props (`_BaseMap`, `_SpecGlossMap`, `unity_Lightmaps`). Sample bundles rebuilt fresh: `sw-b1-squad` 23.5 KB, `sw-cis-aat` 23.5 KB, `sw-rep-clone-engineer` 47.9 KB — build log reports `Total compressed size 22.8–47.0 KB / uncompressed 103.6–152.6 KB` per bundle (NOT `Shaders 0.0 kb`). The `sw-rep-clone-engineer` prefab references material GUID `173ab220…` = its `-primary` URP/Lit material.
- **Note:** URP 12.1.15's `MaterialPostprocessor.OnPostprocessAllAssets` throws a benign `IndexOutOfRangeException` during headless `SaveAssets`; it does NOT prevent persistence (disk `.mat` files verified URP/Lit). Copied all rebuilt unit/building bundles + `.manifest` (158 files) into `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/bundles/`. NOT deployed — orchestrator reconciles + deploys + verifies in-game.

### Fixed — SW building bundles now use URP Lit shader to prevent SRP batch crash
- **Switched procedural Star Wars building bundle material shader from Built-in `Standard` to URP `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit`** with fallback to `Universal Render Pipeline/Simple Lit` during assetbundle build, and switched tinting to `SetColor("_BaseColor", tint)` to keep `Hybrid Renderer V2` SRP batching compatibility.
- Rebuilt all 12 Star Wars building bundles on branch `feat/sw-building-bundles-20260531` using headless `Unity 2021.3.45f1` from `scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder` and confirmed the build log includes `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit`.

