@@ -7,6 +7,12 @@
 
 ## [Unreleased]
 
+### Added — Cursor theming for Star Wars runtime UI
+- Added runtime cursor theming in `src/Runtime` via new `src/Runtime/UI/TcCursorApplicator.cs`.
+- Cursor visuals now apply at menu and gameplay scene entry points (`Plugin.OnSceneLoaded`, `Plugin.OnActiveSceneChanged`, `RuntimeDriver.OnRuntimeDriverSceneChanged`) and update continuously from runtime input state (`RuntimeDriver.Initialize` loop) through `Cursor.SetCursor`.
+- Added Star Wars cursor assets to pack UI path: `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/ui/cursor_default.png`, `cursor_attack.png`, and `cursor_target.png`.
+- The runtime cursor pipeline resolves assets from deployed packs (`BepInEx/dinoforge_packs/warfare-starwars/assets/ui`) and logs non-fatal diagnostics when resources are missing.
+
 ### Fixed — URP material crash guard in AssetSwap
 - **Prevented a live material crash path on HRV2/URP when a swapped bundle material uses legacy shaders** — `TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` now validates the resolved material shader before assigning it to `RenderMesh`. Materials whose shader name is not prefixed with `Universal Render Pipeline/` and that do not expose SRP batcher support via `FindPassTagValue` are skipped from live material assignment, while mesh swaps still proceed when valid. Skipped bundles log once (`[AssetSwap] skipped material swap for X: shader Y not HRV2-compatible`) and fallback to no-op material assignment. Crash-risk runtime writes are therefore prevented without blocking mesh-only swaps. File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`.
 
